**Flexbox** (Flexible Box Layout) and **CSS Grid** are the core layout systems of modern CSS.

**KEY DIFFERENCES:**
- **Flexbox (1-Dimensional)**: Excellent for laying out items in a single direction (row OR column). Great for headers, nav bars, menus, and centering items.
- **CSS Grid (2-Dimensional)**: Designed for complex page structures with columns AND rows simultaneously. Great for full page layouts, dashboards, and photo galleries.

**FLEXBOX vs GRID CSS DEFINITIONS:**
```css
/* Flexbox layout */
.header-nav {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
}

/* Grid layout */
.dashboard-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr;
  grid-template-rows: 60px auto;
  gap: 15px;
}
```

